CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. B10 reads: "Chi Delta Mu Fraternity Entertains Lavishly - Dr. Charles Bookert, far left, chairman of the dinner-dance, and guests. Mrs. Bookert, eighth from left, and guests."  Portion of accompanying article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. A7 by Toki Schalk Johnson reads:"Wednesday brought forth the annual dinner dance given by the Chi Delta Mu Fraternity in beautifully decorated New Arena."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eight men, including Dr. Charles Bookert, far left and Bill Nunn Jr., and eight women, including Mrs. Charles Bookert, eighth from left, and Frances Bell Nunn and Lois Weaver Watson seated at rectangular banquet table for Chi Delta Mu dinner dance in New Arena Supper Club
